<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/956430-how-is-this-book-if-at-all-different">How is this book, if at all, different from the movie?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_956430'><a id="like_count_community_question_956430" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/956430?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">8 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F223380.Stories_of_Your_Life_and_Others">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/956430-how-is-this-book-if-at-all-different">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/956430-how-is-this-book-if-at-all-different">See all 8 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/20563569-rachita-sharma"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1609304793i/20563569._UX100_CR0,14,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/20563569-rachita-sharma">Rachita Sharma</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    Apart from some minor changes in the storyline, there is also difference in the central focal point of the book and the movie. While the movie focuses<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    Apart from some minor changes in the storyline, there is also difference in the central focal point of the book and the movie. While the movie focuses on emotional aspects of the story, the book also places an equal if not higher focus on the technical aspects of how the world functions (differently for heptapods and humans) and how your language can alter the way you perceive this world.<br /><br />In the book, there are detailed explanations around how the heptapods have a non-linear sense of time which also reflects in their written language (heptapod B), and why/how Louise, after learning heptapod B language, starts perceving the world in a completely different way. Movie misses this aspect and leaves it to the viewers' interpretation. In the movie, it is also not made extremely clear why Louise starts seeing the future. You will get these answers in the book, explained in both linguistics as well as physics terms. If you care only about the emotional aspects of the story, then watching the movie should be enough, but if you want to understand the underlying details and differences in the understanding of the world between heptapods and humans, then reading the book is worth it. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
