<div id="review_927421205" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/927421205" />
    <a title="Rob" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3901371-rob"><img alt="Rob" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1314157360p2/3901371.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/927421205?book_show_action=true">May 03, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rob" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rob" href="/user/show/3901371-rob">Rob</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3901371-rob?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3901371-rob?shelf=science-fiction">science-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3901371-rob?shelf=kindle">kindle</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer927421205" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8198795769596808429">No accounting for taste especially your own.<br/>This book has had rave reviews and not from the usual sources. It has won a few well regarded awards. And I hated it.<br/>The overall writing style I found to be flat. The characterisation was awful. Has this author ever met another human and talked to them? It has the same warmth as an IT support manual.<br/>Quite a bit of science fiction is not exactly literary but it more than makes up for it by exploring ideas. This collection of short stories had ideas but </span>
  <span id="freeText8198795769596808429" style="display:none">No accounting for taste especially your own.<br />This book has had rave reviews and not from the usual sources. It has won a few well regarded awards. And I hated it.<br />The overall writing style I found to be flat. The characterisation was awful. Has this author ever met another human and talked to them? It has the same warmth as an IT support manual.<br />Quite a bit of science fiction is not exactly literary but it more than makes up for it by exploring ideas. This collection of short stories had ideas but maybe a third had overt religious overtones. Not just the way religious ideas, philosophy and science may have a meeting point, no just straight up religion.<br />There was no wit to the stories, no fun with ideas. The narrative voice was a flat monotone only relieved by vain attempts at horror. <br />I just don't get this book but yet so many others do.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="8198795769596808429" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


